# Fishmarket v3 – Routes

All routes live under `src/app/` using the Next.js App Router. Update this file whenever routes are added, removed, or restructured.

## `ROUTES` constant

All route paths are defined in **`src/lib/routes.ts`** as the `ROUTES` object. Always import from there instead of hardcoding path strings:

```ts
import { ROUTES } from "@/lib/routes";

router.push(ROUTES.createListing);   // "/create-listing"
<Link href={ROUTES.home}>Home</Link> // "/"
```

When adding a new route, add its path to `ROUTES` first, then reference the key everywhere.

## Route table

| Key | Path | File | Description |
|-----|------|------|-------------|
| `home` | `/` | `src/app/page.tsx` | Component showcase (design system demo) |
| `shop` | `/shop` | — | Shop (placeholder) |
| `createListing` | `/create-listing` | `src/app/create-listing/page.tsx` | Listing flow entry — "Advance listing" intro screen (Figma node `394:1125`). Decorative image grid, heading, and Create CTA. |
| `createListingForm` | `/create-listing/form` | `src/app/create-listing/form/page.tsx` | Advance listing form (Figma node `417:1722`). react-hook-form + zod. MediaDropzone, title, description, price, condition, category, variants (via VariantDrawer + VariantList). Submits to Firestore and Storage (including variant images). |
| `map` | `/map` | — | Map (placeholder) |
| `profile` | `/profile` | — | Profile (placeholder) |
